    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera 4S represents a pinnacle of the naturally aspirated, widebody flat-six era. Powered by a 3.6L boxer engine featuring VarioCam Plus valve timing, the powerplant is mated to a precise 6-speed manual transaxle and a viscous-coupling all-wheel-drive system. The mechanical integrity is superlative; the IMS bearing has been proactively addressed with a dual-row ceramic retrofit, and the rear main seal remains bone dry. The chassis retains its factory-delivered rigidity, supported by pristine Bilstein dampers and original alloy subframes. The paint depth is consistent across all panels, showing zero imperfections, while the cabin features supple, uncompressed leather bolsters and a functional, pixel-perfect instrument cluster. This is a turn-key, collector-grade specimen for the technical purist.",
